300 g Tilapia Fillets
6 unit Flour Tortillas
113 g Green Cabbage, shredded
56 g Carrot, julienned
1 unit Green Onion
1 unit Garlic, cloves
3 tbsp Sour Cream
2 tbsp Mayonnaise
1 tbsp Enchilada Spice Blend
2 tsp Sugar*
1 tbsp Oil*
0.13 tsp Pepper*
0.13 tsp Salt*
1 tbsp Rice Vinegar

Before starting, wash and dry all produce. Garlic guide for Step 5: 1/4 tsp (1/2 tsp) mild, 1/2 tsp (1 tsp) medium and 1 tsp (2 tsp) extra! Peel, then mince or grate garlic. Thinly slice green onion.

Add mayo, vinegar, and 1 tsp (2 tsp) sugar to a medium bowl. Season with salt and pepper, then whisk to combine. Add cabbage, carrots and half the green onions, then toss to combine.

Pat tilapia dry with paper towels. Add tilapia, Enchilada Spice Blend and 1 tsp (2 tsp) sugar to a large bowl. Season with salt and pepper, then toss to coat.

Heat a large non-stick pan over medium-high heat. When the pan is hot, add 1 tbsp (2 tbsp) oil, then tilapia. Fry tilapia, flipping halfway, until cooked through 2-3 min per side.\*\* Transfer to a plate and set aside.

Add sour cream, 1/2 tbsp (1 tbsp) water and 1/2 tsp (1 tsp) garlic to a small bowl. (NOTE: Reference garlic guide.) Season with salt and pepper, then stir to combine.

Wrap tortillas in paper towels.Microwave until warm and flexible, 30 sec-1 min. (TIP: You can skip this step if you don't want to warm tortillas!)Divide tortillas between plates. Top with some coleslaw, then tilapia. Dollop garlic crema over top.Sprinkle with remaining green onions.